title: Amplify Podcast Network
description: This project supports the development of an open source scholarly podcast preservation tool. The project aims to develop an institutionally-integrated tool researchers can use to archive their episodes with rich metadata while supporting the preservation of their podcasts within institutional repositories.
subject: Podcasts;Digital preservation

title: Fragmenting the West Coast through Asian Canadian Poetry
description: This project examines how contemporary Asian Canadian poets relate their experiences of migration, culture, and the environment on the West Coast. The project will concentrate on the writings of a diverse group of prominent and emerging authors. Through a close analysis of their poems and related writing, "Fragmenting the West Coast Through Asian Canadian Poetry" constructs a radical, revisionary cartography of British Columbia that demonstrates the cultural and historical importance of the unique narratives of Asian Canadians in this region.
subject: Poetry; Asian Canadian; British Columbia
